[49m[38;5;9m- 11    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m That conversation is not happening, and the reason it is not happening is not that her care team is bad. It is that the cognitive job of integrating a nine-year longitudinal trajectory across multiple variables, accounting for treatment effects, factoring in known disease-specific progression rates, and communicating future-state uncertainty in a way that is actionable, is not the cognitive job that an outpatient nephrology visit is structured to do. Each visit is a snapshot. The trajectory lives across snapshots and across the analytic gap that the EHR was never designed to bridge.
