[49m[38;5;9m- 628     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Multi-modal data integration.** Trajectory models gain meaningfully from integrating imaging-derived measurements (kidney volume on MRI for ADPKD, brain volumetrics for neurodegenerative diseases, tumor volumes for oncology), genetic markers (PKD1 versus PKD2 mutation, APOE genotype, tumor mutational burden), and structured assessments (UPDRS, MMSE, EDSS). The pipeline as drawn handles structured EHR data well; integrating imaging and genetics requires additional ingestion paths, additional harmonization (DICOM-derived measurements via Recipe 9.x; genomic data through specialized stores), and additional joins in the cohort harmonization step. Production systems for diseases where these modalities matter must have these integrations or they leave the most informative signals on the floor.
